HEADWORD: Shruff
<hw>Shruff</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Scruff</er>,
<er>Scurf</er>.]</ety> <def>Rubbish.</def>
<specif>Specifically:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Dross or refuse of
metals.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Light, dry wood, or
stuff used for fuel.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

